    behavior: "These neurons tend to activate early in the processing pipeline, where token-level polarity is established before deeper semantic integration. They often co-activate with Identity neurons when a named entity is being positively attributed — for example, 'Einstein was a physicist' triggers both Affirmation and Identity.Person signals together.",
    example: "In Llama 3.1 8B, Boolean.Affirmation neurons fire strongly on prompts like 'The answer is yes' and 'Water does conduct electricity.' They remain quieter on hedged statements like 'Water may conduct electricity' — where Entropy.Ambiguity neurons take over instead.",
